  50:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** File    : SEGGER_RTT.c
  51:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** Purpose : Implementation of SEGGER real-time transfer (RTT) which
  52:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           allows real-time communication on targets which support
  53:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           debugger memory accesses while the CPU is running.
  54:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** Revision: $Rev: 24715 $
  55:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  56:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** Additional information:
  57:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           Type "int" is assumed to be 32-bits in size
  58:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           H->T    Host to target communication
  59:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           T->H    Target to host communication
  60:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  61:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           RTT channel 0 is always present and reserved for Terminal usage.
  62:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           Name is fixed to "Terminal"
  63:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  64:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           Effective buffer size: SizeOfBuffer - 1
  65:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  66:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           WrOff == RdOff:       Buffer is empty
  67:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           WrOff == (RdOff - 1): Buffer is full
  68:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           WrOff >  RdOff:       Free space includes wrap-around
  69:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           WrOff <  RdOff:       Used space includes wrap-around
  70:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****           (WrOff == (SizeOfBuffer - 1)) && (RdOff == 0):  
  71:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c ****                                 Buffer full and wrap-around after next byte
  72:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  73:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  74:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  75:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
  76:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** 
  77:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** #include "SEGGER_RTT.h"
