 995:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 996:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *       SEGGER_RTT_WriteDownBufferNoLock
 997:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
 998:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
 999:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Stores a specified number of characters in SEGGER RTT
1000:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    control block inside a <Down> buffer.
1001:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    SEGGER_RTT_WriteDownBufferNoLock does not lock the application.
1002:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Used to do the same operation that J-Link does, to transfer 
1003:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    RTT data from other channels, such as TCP/IP or UART.
1004:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1005:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
1006:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Down"-buffer to be used.
1007:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    pBuffer      Pointer to character array. Does not need to point to a \0 terminated string.
1008:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    NumBytes     Number of bytes to be stored in the SEGGER RTT control block.
1009:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1010:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Return value
1011:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Number of bytes which have been stored in the "Down"-buffer.
1012:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1013:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Notes
1014:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (1) Data is stored according to buffer flags.
1015:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (2) For performance reasons this function does not call Init()
1016:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        and may only be called after RTT has been initialized.
1017:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        Either by calling SEGGER_RTT_Init() or calling another RTT API function first.
1018:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1019:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Additional information
1020:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    This function must not be called when J-Link might also do RTT.
1021:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
