1077:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1078:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
1079:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Stores a specified number of characters in SEGGER RTT
1080:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    control block which is then read by the host.
1081:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    SEGGER_RTT_WriteNoLock does not lock the application.
1082:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1083:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
1084:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Up"-buffer to be used (e.g. 0 for "Terminal").
1085:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    pBuffer      Pointer to character array. Does not need to point to a \0 terminated string.
1086:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    NumBytes     Number of bytes to be stored in the SEGGER RTT control block.
1087:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1088:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Return value
1089:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Number of bytes which have been stored in the "Up"-buffer.
1090:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1091:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Notes
1092:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (1) Data is stored according to buffer flags.
1093:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (2) For performance reasons this function does not call Init()
1094:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        and may only be called after RTT has been initialized.
1095:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *        Either by calling SEGGER_RTT_Init() or calling another RTT API function first.
1096:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
