1215:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1216:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Function description
1217:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Stores string in SEGGER RTT control block.
1218:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    This data is read by the host.
1219:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1220:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Parameters
1221:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Up"-buffer to be used (e.g. 0 for "Terminal").
1222:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    s            Pointer to string.
1223:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1224:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Return value
1225:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    Number of bytes which have been stored in the "Up"-buffer.
1226:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *
1227:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *  Notes
1228:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (1) Data is stored according to buffer flags.
1229:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (2) String passed to this function has to be \0 terminated
1230:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** *    (3) \0 termination character is *not* stored in RTT buffer
1231:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT.c **** */
